**Standard page structure**

Use this structure unless otherwise instructed:

1. Page heading on the top
2. Filters below page heading
3. Metrics if applicable
4. Tabs if applicable

**Creating pages**

1. Never add streamlit page config unless specifically instructed.
2. Always use absolute imports, never relative imports.


**Headers, text and captions**

1. Use streamlit native text formating when possible: st.title, st.header, and st.subheader for different levels of headings. st.markdown for regular text and st.caption for explanatory text.
2. Never use in-line icons with markdown, unless instructed specifically.
3. Use st.divider() instead of a st.markdown() created horizontal line.